    "body": "It requires implementation of https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/issues/694\r\n\r\n> New spec:\r\n> \r\n> 1. When a user starts creating a new 1 on 1 or ad-hoc group chat, they should be shown at the beginning (left) of the add user pill input field, using the 'king pill'.  In this state there is no \"X\" on the 'king pill' because it doesn't make any sense for a user to remove themself from a group chat before they have even started it.\r\n> 2. When a user who is not an admin enters the 'edit mode', all users who are already in the chat are represented by grey pillis without an \"X\".\r\n> 3. When the admin enters the edit mode, there are \"x\"'s on all pills excluding their own 'king pill'.\r\n> 4. Everybody in the ad-hoc group chat who is not the admin will see a \"Add to Group\" menu option instead of an \"Add / remove from group\" menu option (only the ad-hoc group chat admin will see this in the menu).  And when someone who is not the admin selects the \"Add to Group\" menu option, they shouldn't see \"X\" on the right of the pills belonging to users who are already in the ad-hoc group chat.\r\n> \r\n> ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/97019400/170651974-728d68c2-6cd8-4aa5-af20-8cd863a855b9.png)\r\n\r\nThe scope of the current task is:\r\n- Only admin can see the option.\r\n- Admin is not displayed in the group chat panel.\r\n\r\nNew specs will be addressed here: https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/5941",
